UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 926
1 AN ACT relating to pedestrians.
2 WHEREAS, the presence of individuals remaining physically stationary in narrow
3 medians, highway shoulders, and exit ramps presents a significant safety risk to both
4 pedestrians and motorists; and
5 WHEREAS, at the present time, Kentucky lacks a clear statewide standard in the
6 law for this behavior, and law enforcement agencies have reported an increase in
7 dangerous pedestrian presence in non-pedestrian portions of the state-maintained right-
8 of-way; and
9 WHEREAS, the General Assembly wishes to promote roadway safety by restricting
10 stationary pedestrian behavior in rights-of-way that are not designed or designated for
11 pedestrian use, while allowing local governments, in coordination with the Kentucky
12 Transportation Cabinet, to authorize limited exceptions through objective and safety-
13 based permitting;
14 NOW, THEREFORE,
15 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
16 SECTION 1. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 189 IS CREATED TO
17 READ AS FOLLOWS:
18 (1) As used in this section:
19 (a) "Local government" means any city, county, consolidated local
20 government, urban-county government, charter county government, or
21 unified local government; and
22 (b) "State-maintained right-of-way" means any land, property, or
23 infrastructure under the jurisdiction or maintenance of the Kentucky
24 Transportation Cabinet that is used by the public for transportation
25 purposes, including but not limited to travel lanes, paved and unpaved
26 shoulders, medians, entrance and exit ramps, and adjacent grassy or
27 drainage areas not designated for pedestrian use.
Page 1 of 6
