UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 926
1 (2) Except as provided in subsection (3) or (4) of this section, a person shall not sit,
2 kneel, recline, stand, or remain physically stationary in any portion of a state-
3 maintained right-of-way that is not designated for pedestrian use.
4 (3) Subsection (2) of this section shall not apply to:
5 (a) Individuals experiencing a medical emergency;
6 (b) Individuals involved in a vehicle-related emergency, provided they remain
7 in the immediate area of the vehicle;
8 (c) Emergency personnel or public utility workers performing their official
9 duties; or
10 (d) Persons located within a pedestrian-designated area such as a sidewalk,
11 marked crosswalk, or transit stop.
12 (4) A local government may by ordinance authorize limited exceptions to subsection
13 (2) of this section if:
14 (a) The ordinance:
15 1. Establishes a clear process by which a person may request and receive
16 authorization by the local government to act in accordance with any
17 adopted exception;
18 2. Applies uniformly; and
19 3. Is based solely on objective criteria that is ministerially applied;
20 (b) Authorization granted by the local government to any person is limited in
21 duration and scope;
22 (c) The local government maintains records of each authorization provided
23 under this subsection that includes a statement of justification for its
24 issuance; and
25 (d) Any ordinance adopted under this subsection, and any authorization
26 granted pursuant thereto, comply with this section and any administrative
27 regulations promulgated by the Transportation Cabinet.
