1 (5) The Transportation Cabinet may promulgate administrative regulations in
2 accordance with KRS Chapter 13A to define minimum pedestrian safety
3 standards for state-maintained rights-of-way.
4 Section 2. KRS 189.570 is amended to read as follows:
5 (1) Pedestrians shall obey the instruction of any official traffic control devices
6 specifically applicable to them, unless otherwise directed by a police officer or
7 other officially designated persons.
8 (2) Pedestrians shall be subject to traffic and pedestrian control signals as provided in
9 KRS 189.231 and 189.338.
10 (3) At all other places, pedestrians shall be accorded the privileges and shall be subject
11 to the restrictions stated in this chapter.
12 (4) When traffic control signals are not in place or in operation the operator of a vehicle
13 shall yield the right-of-way, slowing down or stopping if need be to so yield, to a
14 pedestrian crossing the roadway upon which the vehicle is traveling, or when the
15 pedestrian is approaching so closely from the opposite half of the roadway as to be
16 in danger.
17 (5) Whenever any vehicle is stopped at a marked crosswalk or at any unmarked
18 crosswalk at an intersection, to permit a pedestrian to cross the roadway, the
19 operator of any other vehicle approaching from the rear shall not overtake and pass
20 the stopped vehicle.
21 (6) (a) Every pedestrian crossing a roadway at a point other than within a marked
22 crosswalk or within an unmarked crosswalk at an intersection shall yield the
23 right-of-way to all vehicles upon the roadway.
24 (b) Any pedestrian crossing a roadway at a point where a pedestrian tunnel or
25 overhead pedestrian crossing has been provided shall yield the right-of-way to
26 all vehicles upon the roadway.
27 (c) Between adjacent intersections within the city limits of every city at which
Page 3 of 6
XXXX 10/29/2025 1:17 PM Jacketed

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 926
1 traffic control signals are in operation, pedestrians shall not cross at any place
2 except in a marked crosswalk.
3 (d) Notwithstanding other provisions of this subsection or the provisions of any
4 local ordinance, every operator of a vehicle shall exercise due care to avoid
5 colliding with any pedestrian and shall give warning by sounding the horn
6 when necessary and shall exercise proper precaution upon observing a child
7 or an obviously confused or incapacitated person upon a roadway.
8 (7) The operator of a[No] vehicle shall not drive[at any time be driven] through or
9 within a safety zone.
10 (8) The operator of a vehicle shall yield the right-of-way to any pedestrian on a
11 sidewalk.
12 (9) A[No] pedestrian shall not suddenly leave a curb or other place of safety and walk
13 or run into the path of a vehicle which is so close as to constitute an immediate
14 hazard.
15 (10) A[No] pedestrian shall not cross a roadway intersection diagonally unless
16 authorized by official traffic control devices; and, when authorized to cross
17 diagonally, pedestrians shall cross only in accordance with the official traffic
18 control devices pertaining to such crossing movements.
19 (11) Pedestrians shall move, whenever practicable, upon the right half of crosswalks.
20 (12) Where a sidewalk is provided and its use is practicable, it shall be unlawful for any
21 pedestrian to walk along and upon an adjacent roadway.
22 (13) Where a sidewalk is not available, any pedestrian walking along and upon a
23 highway shall walk only on a shoulder, as far as practicable from the edge of the
24 roadway.
25 (14) Where neither a sidewalk nor a shoulder is available, any pedestrian walking on or
26 along a highway shall walk as near as practicable to an outside edge of the roadway,
27 and, if on a two-way roadway shall walk only on the left side of the roadway.
