UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 926
1 (15) Except as otherwise provided in this chapter, any pedestrian upon a roadway shall
2 yield the right-of-way to all vehicles upon the roadway.
3 (16) A pedestrian who is under the influence of alcohol or any kind of drug to a degree
4 which renders himself or herself a hazard shall not walk or be upon a highway
5 except on a sidewalk.
6 (17) A[No] pedestrian shall not enter or remain upon any bridge or approach thereto
7 beyond the bridge signal, gate, or barrier, after a bridge operation signal indication
8 has been given.
9 (18) A[No] pedestrian shall not pass through, around, over, or under any crossing gate or
10 barrier at a railroad grade crossing or bridge while such gate or barrier is closed or
11 is being opened or closed.
12 (19) A[No] person shall not stand in a roadway for the purpose of soliciting a ride.
13 (20) A[No] person shall not stand on a roadway for the purpose of soliciting
14 employment or business from the occupant of any vehicle.
15 (21) A[No] person shall not stand on a highway for the purpose of soliciting
16 contributions unless such soliciting is designated by the presence of a traffic control
17 device or warning signal or an emergency vehicle or public safety vehicle as
18 defined in KRS 189.910 making use of the flashing, rotating or oscillating red, blue,
19 or yellow lights on such devices or vehicles.
20 (22) A[No] person shall not stand on or in proximity to a street or highway for the
21 purpose of soliciting the watching or guarding of any vehicle while parked or about
22 to be parked on a street or highway.
23 (23) A person shall not occupy any portion of a state-maintained right-of-way in
24 violation of Section 2 of this Act.
25 (24) Upon the immediate approach of an emergency vehicle equipped with[,] and
26 operating[,] one (1) or more flashing, rotating, or oscillating red or blue lights[,]
27 visible under normal conditions from a distance of five hundred feet (500) feet to
