1 the front of such vehicle, and the operator of which is giving audible signal by
2 siren, exhaust whistle, or bell, every pedestrian shall yield the right-of-way to the
3 emergency vehicle.
4 (25)[(24)] This section shall not relieve the operator of an emergency vehicle from the
5 duty to:
6 (a) Drive with due regard for the safety of all persons using the highway; and
7 (b) [nor from the duty to ]Exercise due care to avoid colliding with any
8 pedestrian.
